            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Parser errors are usually fatal for the compiler, with only a few exceptions, but I wouldn't mind having a scanner-local setting that disables the `raise` in `PyrexScanner.error()`. Note that the attribute needs to be added to the `Scanning.pxd` as well. I think it's enough to add that option to the `TreeFragment` API for now, if that suits your use case. It can be added to other interfaces of the parser later, if necessary.\r\n\r\nPR welcome.",
